<paragraph id="0F64CC39FFB846051E8DF3B751751A99" blockId="7.[136,1452,1191,1686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051E8DF3B7530A18CD" bold="true" box="[189,265,1192,1218]" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Notes:</emphasis>
The nucleotide base pair differences of ITS, LSU and mtSSU sequences are compared between our new species and members of 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051F9AF3D3504F18EA" authorityName="Crous" authorityYear="2017" box="[426,588,1228,1253]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051F9AF3D3504F18EA" box="[426,588,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fitzroyomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="4259F982FFB846051C6EF3D450BA18E9" box="[606,697,1227,1254]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[136,224,916,940]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2 Nucleotide differences in the ITS, LSU and mtSSU (not trimmed sequence) of Fitzroyomyces species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5BA49CB1FFB846051EB8F48B573F1FA3" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" tableUuid="5BA49CB1FFB846051EB8F48B573F1FA3">Table 2</tableCitation>
). The new taxon was established based on the recommendations outlined by 
<bibRefCitation id="6B4AB1C8FFB846051F23F3EF50261905" author="Jeewon, R. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[275,549,1263,1290]" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" pagination="1669 - 1677" refId="ref9106" refString="Jeewon, R. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2016) Establishing species boundaries and new taxa among fungi: recommendations to resolve taxonomic ambiguities. Mycosphere 7: 1669 - 1677. https: // doi. org / 10.5943 / mycosphere / 7 / 11 / 4" type="journal article" year="2016">Jeewon &amp; Hyde (2016)</bibRefCitation>
. We also compared the morphology of our strain with 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051A91F3EF57701906" box="[1185,1395,1264,1289]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cyperacearum">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051A91F3EF57701906" box="[1185,1395,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit. cyperacearum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051BB4F3EF500C1922" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051BB4F3EF534A1922" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hyaloseptisporus">Fit. hyaloseptisporus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051F64F20B500C1922" box="[340,527,1299,1325]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pandanicola">Fit. pandanicola</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051C75F20B50FD1922" box="[581,766,1300,1325]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051C75F20B50FD1922" box="[581,766,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="4259F982FFB846051D3DF20C51681921" box="[781,875,1299,1326]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="9.[136,224,158,182]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="TABLE 3. Morphological comparison of Fitzroyomyces species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5BA49CB1FFB6460B1EB8F781513E1CB8" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" tableUuid="5BA49CB1FFB6460B1EB8F781513E1CB8">Table. 3</tableCitation>
). The differences between 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051AA9F20B57A81922" authorityName="R. F. Xu &amp; Tibpromma" authorityYear="2022" box="[1177,1451,1299,1325]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xishuangbannaensis">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051AA9F20B57A81922" box="[1177,1451,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit. xishuangbannaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051E86F2275380195E" box="[182,387,1336,1361]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cyperacearum">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051E86F2275380195E" box="[182,387,1336,1361]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit. cyperacearum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are that the larger apothecia (235–430 × 200–520 μm vs. 201–260 × 210–310 μm), wider exciple (17–70 μm vs. 20–55 μm), narrower paraphyses (17–70 μm vs. 24–54 μm), longer asci (110–150 × 10–20 μm vs. 160– 180 × 10–20 μm), longer, and fusiform ascospore guttulate with more septation. 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051A2EF29F57A81996" authorityName="R. F. Xu &amp; Tibpromma" authorityYear="2022" box="[1054,1451,1407,1433]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xishuangbannaensis">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051A2EF29F57A81996" box="[1054,1451,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fitzroyomyces xishuangbannaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051F29F2BB500B19B2" box="[281,520,1443,1469]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hyaloseptisporus">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051F29F2BB500B19B2" box="[281,520,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit. hyaloseptisporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in larger apothecia (235–430 × 200–520 μm vs. 140–200 × 150–200 μm), wider exciple (20–55 μm vs. 6–20 μm), smaller asci (160–180 × 10–20 μm vs. 165–200 × 10–25 μm) and ascospores (90– 180 × 2–4 μm vs. 150–200 × 3.5–6 μm), further, ascospores are fuliform with more septation in 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051A8FF2F357AF1A0A" box="[1215,1452,1515,1542]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hyaloseptisporus">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051A8FF2F356E31A0A" box="[1215,1248,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051ADEF2F457AF1A0A" box="[1262,1452,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">hyaloseptisporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whereas 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051EDBF10F53FF1A26" authorityName="R. F. Xu &amp; Tibpromma" authorityYear="2022" box="[235,508,1551,1577]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xishuangbannaensis">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051EDBF10F53FF1A26" box="[235,508,1551,1577]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit. xishuangbannaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses filiform, hyaline, multiseptate ascospores finely guttulate when immature (
<bibRefCitation id="6B4AB1C8FFB846051EBFF12C534B1A41" author="Wei, D. P. &amp; Wanasinghe, D. N. &amp; Gentekaki, E. &amp; Thiyagaraja, V. &amp; Lumyong, S. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[143,328,1587,1614]" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" pagination="880" refId="ref11388" refString="Wei, D. P., Wanasinghe, D. N., Gentekaki, E., Thiyagaraja, V., Lumyong, S. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2021) Morphological and phylogenetic appraisal of novel and extant taxa of Stictidaceae from Northern Thailand. Journal of Fungi 7: 880. https: // doi. org / 10.3390 / jof 7100880" type="journal article" year="2021">
Wei 
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051EF8F12B53001A42" box="[200,259,1587,1613]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051F6FF12B50701A42" authorityName="R. F. Xu &amp; Tibpromma" authorityYear="2022" box="[351,627,1587,1613]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="xishuangbannaensis">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051F6FF12B50701A42" box="[351,627,1587,1613]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit. xishuangbannaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051C9FF12B51681A42" box="[687,875,1588,1613]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051C9FF12B51681A42" box="[687,875,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the same geographical distribution in 
<collectingCountry id="77CC8CA9FFB846051B58F12C57A81A42" box="[1384,1451,1587,1613]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6B4AB1C8FFB846051EA0F14753311A7D" author="Lu, L. &amp; Tibpromma, S. &amp; Karunaratthan, S. C. &amp; Thiyagaraja, V. &amp; Xu, J. C. &amp; Jayawardena, R. S. &amp; Lumyong, S. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[144,306,1623,1650]" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" pagination="111 - 124" refId="ref9414" refString="Lu, L., Tibpromma, S., Karunaratthan, S. C., Thiyagaraja, V., Xu, J. C., Jayawardena, R. S., Lumyong, S. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2021) Taxonomic and phylogenic appraisal of one novel species and one new record of Stictidaceae from coffee in Yunnan Province, China. Phytotaxa 528: 111 - 124 https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 528.2.4" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lu 
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051E88F14752F11A7E" box="[184,242,1623,1649]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
) however, the two differ in several morphological characteristics such as 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051A45F147572D1A7E" box="[1141,1326,1624,1649]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051A45F147572D1A7E" box="[1141,1326,1624,1649]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fit. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has bigger apothecia, smaller asci, smaller ascospores and septation (
<tableCitation id="4259F982FFB846051D21F164516B1A99" box="[785,872,1659,1686]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="9.[136,224,158,182]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="TABLE 3. Morphological comparison of Fitzroyomyces species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5BA49CB1FFB6460B1EB8F781513E1CB8" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" tableUuid="5BA49CB1FFB6460B1EB8F781513E1CB8">Table 3</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47C19FB2FFB846051EB8F1DC57A8141D" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" type="key">
<paragraph id="0F64CC39FFB846051EB8F1DC500C1AD2" blockId="7.[136,527,1731,1758]" box="[136,527,1731,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">
<heading id="542C7B55FFB846051EB8F1DC500C1AD2" bold="true" box="[136,527,1731,1758]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" reason="1">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051EB8F1DC500C1AD2" bold="true" box="[136,527,1731,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">
A key to species in 
<taxonomicName id="C8DBB7BAFFB846051F59F1DC500C1AD2" authorityName="Crous" authorityYear="2017" box="[361,527,1731,1757]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stictidaceae" genus="Fitzroyomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ostropales" pageId="7" pageNumber="260" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3DAF102BFFB846051F59F1DC500C1AD2" bold="true" box="[361,527,1731,1757]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="260">Fitzroyomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
